constraints:

1. NOT NULL (Enforced)
It ensures a column cannot store NULL values.

2. CHECK ( Enforced)
It ensures values satisfy a condition.

✔ Example: SAL > 0 will be checked strictly

3. PRIMARY KEY (Not fully enforced  )

accepts repeated vale
null will not accepted


4. UNIQUE ( Not enforced)
Duplicate prevention is not strictly enforced.


5. FOREIGN KEY ( Not enforced)
FOREIGN KEY constraint is not enforced in Snowflake.



CREATE OR REPLACE TABLE DEPT(
DNO NUMBER PRIMARY KEY,
DNAME VARCHAR,
LOC VARCHAR
);


CREATE OR REPLACE TABLE EMP
(
EID NUMBER primary key,
ENAME VARCHAR not null,
cno number(10) unique,
SAL NUMBER(10,2) check(sal>0) not null,
DOJ DATE default current_date(),
JOIN_TIME TIMESTAMP default current_timestamp(),
IS_ACTIVE BOOLEAN default true,
DNO NUMBER,
FOREIGN KEY(DNO) REFERENCES DEPT(DNO)
);

